{
  "texts": [
    "Simple simulation experiments show, however, that several hundreds of FA generations are needed for each prompt to yield consistently good approximation of NTP distributions (as measured by nEMD), especially when the NTP distributions are balanced.",
    "When the temperature is different than 1, FA distributions do not converge to the NTP ones: temperatures lower than 1 favor the most likely answer, temperatures higher than 1 result in more balanced distributions.",
    "To assess the variations between these two strategies in our experiments, we compare their results on two different models (Llama-3-70B and Mixtral-8x7B).",
    "The responses provided by the two strategies differ in part.",
    "The answers obtained with FA are more noisy (being stochastic), and somewhat different from their NTP counterparts."
  ]
}